sql:
SELECT players.player_name, tournaments.tournament_name, players.player_experience
FROM players
INNER JOIN tournaments ON players.player_id = tournaments.tournament_id;

external_knowledge:
- "stewards" refers metaphorically to tournament administrators;
- "digital arena" and "virtual battlegrounds" metaphorically describe online tournaments;
- "duration" is expressed as the start and end dates of the tournament;
- "guiding principles" refers to the tournament rules, which may not be present for all tournaments;
- "revelations by the start of the engagement" means ordering by the start date in descending order.

Outstanding players in this context are those whose pairs scored more than 90% in the tournament;
Exceptional performance is defined as having a score percentage over 90;
Pairs consist of two players, each identified by a unique ID.

- Handicap (hcp) is a measure used to equalize players of different skill levels;
- Average rank indicates the typical performance of a pair across various tournaments;
- The pair consists of two players who compete as a team.
